      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LADY SUSPICIOUS (7) turned in a poor effort by her standards last time out when 17 metres away in seventh over 2190m at Maryborough. Form prior to that had been solid. Drawn to enjoy an economical run and might sweat on the sprint lane. Has the class to return to something like her best. BROWN EYED KATE (5) finished eighth at Ararat two runs ago before a comparable effort at her latest appearance over 1690m at Maryborough, beaten 25 metres. Meets a similar quality field and is good enough to win a race of this calibre. ITGETSBETTER (3) last appeared when fourth over 2190m at this track three-and-a-half months ago. Look out for any positive market movement. SUPREME DOLL (2) is worth some thought after her last-start fourth over 2180m at Terang on March 27.",
